What is wrong with the following <q>definition</q> of a limit?
</p>
  <div class="quote"><q>The limit of <m>f(x)</m>, as <m>x</m> approaches <m>a</m>, is <m>K</m></q> means that given any <m>\delta>0</m> there exists <m>\epsilon>0</m> such that whenever <m>|f(x)-K|\lt  \epsilon</m>, we have <m>|x-a|\lt \delta</m>.</div>  <hint><m>\epsilon</m> should be given first, and the restriction 	<m>|x-a|\lt \delta</m> implies <m>|f(x)-K|\lt  \epsilon</m>, not the other way around.</hint> </statement>
</exercise>
  
